                            <comment id="13818221" author="ashakirin" created="Sat, 9 Nov 2013 18:08:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Short note: the code works fine in CXF 2.5.2.&lt;br/&gt;
In 2.5.2 SAAJInInterceptor uses StaxUtils.copy(node, new W3CDOMStreamWriter(part)); to copy message content.&lt;br/&gt;
It seems that problem is caused by the SAAJStreamWriter.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13818963" author="ashakirin" created="Mon, 11 Nov 2013 13:42:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;One additional finding: SAAJInInterceptor not only concatenates digest value in signatures, but it also composes two security header to single one with actor id from the first one, that causes problem to interpret SAML assertion header.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Original and proceeded requests are attached.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
